    <entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>ए मक्षिका! क्या भिनभिनाती हो?</title>
        <published>2022-11-24T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2022-11-24T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        
        <author>
          <name>
            
              Unknown
            
          </name>
        </author>
        
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://hemish.net/poems/e-makshika/"/>
        <id>https://hemish.net/poems/e-makshika/</id>
        
        <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;A little bit of background, how I came up with this poem:
We had a poem in Grade 9 in school (it was in क्षितिज NCERT book), titled &quot;कैदी और कोकिला&quot; which (you can read it &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.hindipyala.com&#x2F;kaidi-aur-kokila&quot;&gt;here&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;) had  primary lines &quot;क्या गाती हो&quot; and &quot;कोकिल बोलो तो&quot;. It was hightly metaphorical poem, and was written by Makhanlal Chaturvedi during his stay in jail during India&#x27;s Independence moment. Our teacher Meena Anand ma&#x27;am asked us to write one such poem in that style, so I came up with this poem titled &quot;ए मक्षिका! क्या भिनभिनाती हो?&quot;. Is it weird, or is it funny, or does it have some deep message (I seriously did not intend to give a deep message, but if you are a hardcore poet, maybe let me know about the deep meaning.)&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;</summary>
        
    </entry>
